sions as critical for V1, so let me double-check what the source actually says before finalizing this.\n\nLooking at the acceptable omissions criteria more carefully, introductory sentences that just enumerate subsections without real explanation seem like they'd fall into that category. The batch applicability note does provide actual context though, not just enumeration. I think this warrants reporting as a minor omission—it's genuinely useful information for understanding the guide's scope, even if it's not a hard constraint.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14233,"cache_read_input_tokens":35069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14233,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ef021470-f16a-488e-8950-0df7813a8cb8","uuid":"47fd49f9-3572-4f17-bc89-4016bbc41091"}
